The only thing I thought I had control of, was ending it completely. I was wrong! I decided to fight one last time. Finally I broke free and got control of myself back. My addiction is still part of me and I can hear it screaming inside me sometimes. But everyday I get stronger and I love myself to much to ever do that to myself again...

 March 2016, I said goodbye to my addiction. I'm proof we can recover. Please don't stop fighting, keep trying, don't give up. People are waiting and wanting you to come back. PLEASE!!! Reach out, if you need to. YOU ARE STRONGER THAN YOU THINK...
